        "title": "JSF Code formatter or Eclipse XML Editor, each tag for new line?",
        "body": "<p>How to format <code>JSF<\/code> code in eclipse?<\/p>\n\n<p>I already try as the following :<\/p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/4527474/format-xml-code-in-eclipse\">Format XML code in Eclipse<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n<p>My <code>XML Editor<\/code> Configuration Setting is  : <\/p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Line width <strong>120<\/strong><\/li>\n<li>Split multiple attributes each on a new like <strong>Checked<\/strong><\/li>\n<li>Align final bracket in mulit-line element tags  <strong>Checked<\/strong><\/li>\n<li>Clear all blank lines <strong>Checked<\/strong><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n<p>If I do <code>Ctrl + Shif + F<\/code>, eclipse format the code as below. <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;tr&gt;\n    &lt;td&gt;&lt;h:outputText value=\"#{label['MANAGE_USER_TITLE']}\"\n            styleClass=\"table-title\" /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;\n\n&lt;/tr&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>My expectation format is, after <code>Ctrl + Shif + F<\/code><\/p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;tr&gt;        \n    &lt;td&gt;\n        &lt;h:outputText value=\"#{label['MANAGE_USER_TITLE']}\" styleClass=\"table-title\" /&gt; \n                ▲\n                This line may be wrap base on line size.\n    &lt;/td&gt;\n&lt;/tr&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>How can I do for that? Is there any plugin? \nI already try <code>HTML Tidy<\/code>, I can only format <code>HTML<\/code>, not <code>JSF<\/code> code.<\/p>\n\n<p><strong>Update<\/strong><\/p>\n\n<p>Picture -1<\/p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/RWwsw.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"><\/p>\n\n<p>Eclipse Setting for Picture-1<\/p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/PRf4E.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"><\/p>\n\n<p>Picture - 2 (I want)<\/p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/4E331.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"><\/p>\n",
